        "client_msg_id": "4cc0159b-256f-4e57-b650-8f78d2952417",
        "text": "How Reward Minting Works: Key Points\n• *It’s a two-phase system:*\n    ◦ *Phase 1 (Creation):* First, non-spendable `AppRewardCoupons` are generated from transaction fees.\n    ◦ *Phase 2 (Minting):* Later, these coupons are redeemed for CC. The redemption value is amplified by a multiplier, which is especially high for \"featured\" apps.\n• *A time-delay is built-in:*\n    ◦ You cannot redeem a coupon immediately. It is tied to a specific \"mining round\" and you must wait for that round to mature before cashing in. Mining round 10 minutes -&gt; Issuing round 20 minutes\n    ◦ There are 3 Mining and 3 issuing rounds running parallel (so 6 active rounds at a time)\n    ◦ This delay prevents system gaming and allows time for the network to calculate the final reward rates for that period.\n• *Rewards are from a shared, fixed pool:*\n    ◦ The system distributes a pre-set budget of coins each round. Your final reward is a share of this pool. Even validator rewards are from the same pool. There are caps on both.\n    ◦ The redemption rate changes every round based on network activity, creating a competitive environment.\n• *Unique economic incentive:*\n    ◦ Featured apps are rewarded from the issuance pool left over by unfeatured apps.\n    ◦ This means rewards for featured apps are highest when overall network activity is _lower_, incentivizing them to be active during quiet periods.\n",
